Gmail Fetch Agent
       ↓
Sender Normalization Agent   (HDFC, ICICI, MMT)
       ↓
Content Summarization Agent  (what is this email about?)
       ↓
Intent Classification Agent (Promotional, Statement, Due Payment, etc.)
       ↓
Company + Label Aggregation Agent


Emails are classified purely based on summarized content, 
not sender heuristics, and then aggregated by company and intent to produce accurate, explainable insights.”


app.py

Orchestrates the Streamlit UI, coordinates all agents, and presents company-wise email classification insights.

gmail_auth.py

Handles Gmail OAuth authentication and safely manages user access tokens.

gmail_client.py

Fetches raw emails from Gmail and extracts sender, subject, date, and body content.

sender_agent.py

Normalizes raw sender strings into clean company or brand names.

summary_agent.py

Summarizes email content into a concise, intent-focused description to reduce noise.

intent_agent.py

Classifies summarized email content into predefined intent categories like Promotional or Bank Statement.

aggregation.py

Aggregates classified emails by company and category to produce actionable counts and trends.
